        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 1.0,
                "text": "Introduction"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 17
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.1,
                "text": "This guideline is in response to variations across MSE in how COVID-19 patients, who have been discharged from level 1 or level 2 respiratory care at one of the MSE hospitals, are identified for follow-up care - and how follow up is conducted."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 18
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.2,
                "text": "Cases will be identified for follow-up in a site specific way:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 19
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Basildon: Using a spreadsheet kept by the division of medicine identifying positive cases."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 20
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Southend: Using positive swabs and positive radiology to identify cases."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 21
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Broomfield: Identifying cases managed by the respiratory team."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 22
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 1.3,
                "text": "Audit  of  follow  up  has  identified  that  around  80%  of  CXR  abnormalities  have resolved by the time of follow up. There are a wide variety of symptoms present including fatigue, psychological, and respiratory symptoms."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 23
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 2.0,
                "text": "Scope"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 24
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 2.1,
                "text": "The purpose of this document is to ensure an equitable approach to post-Covid follow ups and limit variation by introducing MSE-wide guidelines for the follow-up care of Covid-19 patients who have been discharged from any of the MSE hospitals following an admission to a level 1 or level 2 respiratory care."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 25
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 3.0,
                "text": "Definitions"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 26
        },
        {
            "type": "table",
            "sequence_num": 27,
            "data": {
                "num_rows": 4,
                "num_cols": 2,
                "table_items": [
                    {
                        "text": "TERM"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "DEFINITION"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "CXR"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Chest X Ray"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "ITU"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Intensive Care Unit"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "ECMO"
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "Extra Corporeal Membrane Oxygenation."
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 4.0,
                "text": "Role & Responsibilities within the Trust"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 28
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 4.1,
                "text": "It is the responsibility of Consultants to identify patients who have an abnormal CXR associated with COVID-19 infection which requires follow up to ensure resolution."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 29
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 5.0,
                "text": "Key Elements of Policy / Guideline"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 30
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.1,
                "text": "Follow up passports:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 31
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "All patients discharged with COVID -19 are to be given written information regarding self-care follow up passport advise both locally and nationally. All patients discharged will receive a follow up call by their local community team at 6 weeks post discharge to assess any ongoing symptoms related to COVID \u2013 19 and sign post them to relevant help."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 32
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.2,
                "text": "There were concerns about the resource use involved in giving every patient a follow up appointment, given the somewhat overstretched nature of respiratory out- patient services. Therefore, standard follow up has been limited to repeating a CXR in those who have had an abnormal CXR during an admission with COVID-19."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 33
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.3,
                "text": "Chest Radiographs:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 34
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Chest radiographs (CXR) will be requested using a specific COVID follow up indication. It is essential this is included on the request so radiology can direct these images for appropriate reporting. CXRs will then be reported by radiology using prose and, if appropriate, the following codes to indicate that abnormalities have completely resolved, or resolved to the point where there is no ongoing concern: CVCX0: CXR with no concerning features."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 35
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "PCVCX0: CXR which has been compared with a previous image, and has no concerning features."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 36
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The use of such codes will allow members of the administrative team to send a standard letter to those patients in whom there is no ongoing concern. Patients without this code will have their CXR reviewed by a member of the respiratory team and any further investigations (such as a CT scan) or follow up decided on."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 37
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.4,
                "text": "CT scans:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 38
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Computed Tomography (CT) scans will be requested using a specific COVID follow up indication. It is essential this is included on the request so radiology can direct these images for appropriate reporting. CTs will then be reported by radiology using prose and, if appropriate, the following codes to indicate that abnormalities have completely resolved, or resolved to the point where there is no ongoing concern: CVCT0: CXR with no concerning features."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 39
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "PCVCT0: CXR which has been compared with a previous image, and has no concerning features."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 40
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The use of such codes will allow members of the administrative team to send a standard letter to those patients in whom there is no ongoing concern. Patients without this code will have their CT reviewed by a member of the respiratory team and any further investigations or follow up decided on."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 41
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.5,
                "text": "Post ITU patients:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 42
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Patients post-ITU should be followed up, but this should not duplicate ITU or post ECMO clinics that are planned by the Critical Care Team. Follow up will therefore be site specific and provided by the respiratory team as necessary, if not provided by the local ITU. This is outside of the scope of this guideline."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 43
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.6,
                "text": "Other specific concerns:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 44
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "We established the need for guidelines for community colleagues, and information"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 45
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Any additional concerns identified during a patient's admission (such as incidental findings identified on imaging) will be followed up using the relevant guideline for such conditions."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 46
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 6.0,
                "text": "Training Requirements"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 47
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 6.1,
                "text": "No specific training requirements."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 48
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 7.0,
                "text": "Approval and Implementation"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 49
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 7.1,
                "text": "All policies, procedures and guidelines will be approved by the Clinical Advisory Group, which is the specialist group with the authority to approve local guidelines. These will then be forwarded to the Document control team for submission and ratification by the Joint Document Management Group."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 50
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 7.2,
                "text": "It is the author's responsibility to inform the relevant teams of the approved policy documents when they are uploaded to the Trust's Intranets."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 51
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 8.0,
                "text": "Equality Impact Assessment"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 52
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 8.1,
                "text": "The Trust is committed to the provision of a service that is fair, accessible and meets the needs of all individuals."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 53
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "(Refer to appendix 1)"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 54
        },
